First, get your App Service Plan name:
az appservice plan list --resource-group emeka-rg --query "[].name" --output table
It will return something like:
emeka-website-plan
Then create the new Web App pointing to that same plan:
az webapp create --resource-group emeka-rg --plan emeka-website-plan --name fortune-smart-webapp --runtime "NODE|22-lts"
Deploy your files to the new Web App:
az webapp deploy --resource-group emeka-rg --name fortune-smart-static --src-path site.zip --type zip
Result — two separate web apps, one shared plan:
Same App Service Plan (emeka-website-plan)
│
├── emeka-website-txgekkysrjei4    →  production site
│     https://emeka-website-txgekkysrjei4.azurewebsites.net
│
└── emeka-portfolio                →  second site
      https://emeka-portfolio.azurewebsites.net
